  "body": "As I'm looking into #8205 I noticed that, when a verification request is sent, there's no notification about such request.\r\nIf I receive such a request, I wouldn't know about it at all, unless I **accidentally** check either:\r\n\r\n1. The profile view of the contact that might have sent me such a request\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-11-14 11-25-28](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/201636733-36192e92-969a-4f61-b8e7-beebdc33d13b.png)\r\n\r\n2. Or go to Settings -> Messaging -> Contacts and just notice by accident that there's a \"respond to ID request\" deep in the context menu:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-11-14 11-26-16](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/201636943-6aef2961-3d51-4c3b-9532-92abb39e71f1.png)\r\n\r\nThis needs to be improved by a big margin.\r\n\r\n@MishkaRogachev are you aware if this is somehow covered by your work on the notification center?\r\n",
